-- Polymetal Buys Out AngloGold Ashanti From Russian Joint Venture
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2012-02-08T07:26:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-08/polymetal-buys-out-anglogold-ashanti-from-russian-joint-venture.html
Polymetal International Plc, a
Russian gold miner listed in  London , bought out  AngloGold
Ashanti Ltd. (ANG)  from a joint venture that holds rights to the
Veduga deposit in Russia’s Krasnoyarsk region.  Polymetal acquired the 50 percent it didn’t already own for
$20 million including debt, the company said today in a
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
